 🚀 Static Website Deployment on AWS EC2 using NGINX
This guide walks through how to deploy a static website from a GitHub repository onto an AWS EC2 instance using **NGINX**—without needing SSH access (uses EC2 Instance Connect).
- An AWS account
- A public GitHub repo containing static site files (HTML, CSS, JS)
- A running EC2 instance (Ubuntu)

 Connect to EC2 

1. Go to [EC2 Console](https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2)
2. Select your instance
3. Click **“Connect”**
4. Choose **“EC2 Instance Connect”**
5. Click **“Connect”** to open the browser-based terminal

 Install NGINX & Git
### On Ubuntu:

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install nginx git -y

